text editing, build custom controls that manipulate the contents of your editor, and customize the formatting options available. Explore advanced capabilities of AttributedString that help you craft the best text editing experiences.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC22-10107-Get-it-right-to-left":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc22-10107-get-it-right-to-left","kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"Discover how to develop your app so that it can be localized into “right-to-left” languages such as Arabic and Hebrew. We’ll take you through important considerations for these languages, share solutions to challenges, and provide best practices for delivering a great right-to-left experience in your app.","type":"text"}],"title":"Get it right (to left)","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC22-10107-Get-it-right-to-left"},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/280":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/280","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/280","type":"download","checksum":null},"WWDC25.jpg":{"identifier":"WWDC25.jpg","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25.jpg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25","abstract":[{"text":"Xcode 26, Swift 6.2, iOS\/macOS\/tvOS\/visionOS 26.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"New APIs: ","type":"text"},{"code":"Foundation Models","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"AlarmKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"PermissionKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and more.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25","type":"topic","kind":"article","images":[{"identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"WWDC25.jpg","type":"card"}],"role":"collectionGroup","title":"WWDC25"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC21-10109-Whats-new-in-Foundation":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10109-Whats-new-in-Foundation","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc21-10109-whats-new-in-foundation","abstract":[{"text":"Discover how the latest updates to Foundation can help you improve your app’s localization and internationalization support. Find out about the new AttributedString, designed specifically for Swift, and learn how you can use Markdown to apply style to your localized strings. Explore the grammar agreement engine, which automatically fixes up localized strings so they match grammatical gender and pluralization. And we’ll take you through improvements to date and number formatting that simplify complex requirements while also improving performance.","type":"text"}],"role":"sampleCode","title":"What’s new in Foundation"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-222-Enhance-your-apps-multilingual-experience":{"type":"topic","title":"Enhance your app’s multilingual experience","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-222-Enhance-your-apps-multilingual-experience","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a seamless experience for anyone who uses multiple languages. Learn how Language Discovery allows you to optimize your app using a person’s preferred languages. Explore advances in support for right-to-left languages, including Natural Selection for selecting multiple ranges in bidirectional text. We’ll also cover best practices for supporting multilingual scenarios in your app."}],"role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-222-enhance-your-apps-multilingual-experience"},"WWDC25-Icon.png":{"identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"abstract":[{"text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","kind":"symbol","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"role":"collection","title":"WWDC Notes"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}]},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"type":"link","title":"Learn More…","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}}}